      "description": "Solid budget-friendly driver/project with a strong-running engine, smooth-shifting drivetrain, and the kind of mechanical simplicity that makes upkeep straightforward. It shows cosmetic wear and age, but it starts up, pulls well, and has the right bones for someone who wants dependable transportation, a weekend fixer, or a practical beater with plenty of life left. A well-sorted platform with honest character and usable road manners\u2014worth a look if you want something affordable that still feels mechanically capable.",
